        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 7:20PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 720 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Austell, or 8 miles
northeast of Douglasville. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Marietta, Douglasville, City of South Fulton, Smyrna, Powder
Springs, Austell, Lithia Springs, Fair Oaks, Sweetwater Creek State
Park, Vinings, Jim R Miller Park, Six Flags Over Georgia, Sandtown,
and Mableton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
